gui-speedtest (1.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Persistent file logging. Every run writes DEBUG-level details to
    ~/.cache/gui-speedtest/gui-speedtest.log (XDG-compliant, respects
    XDG_CACHE_HOME). Rotating, 5 files x 1 MiB cap. Console remains
    WARNING-level unless --verbose is passed. Makes it possible to
    diagnose "stuck"-looking runs without re-running with extra flags.
  * Log content includes: per-chunk bytes/elapsed/speed, phase start
    and end transitions, cancel requests, socket.shutdown outcomes,
    mirror probe results, and exception tracebacks at DEBUG.
  * No behavioural changes to the speed test itself.

